	<section id="recipe">
		<p> 
			Going back to my culinary adventure in Egypt, back when I
			was still a vegetarian.
			I realised the Egyptians were especially good at making
			falafel, and I wondered why the locals found 
			vegetarians so bizarre when they made such wonderful
			vegetarian dishes!  
			The combination of tahini, falafel and halloumi in a
			wrap was simply genius, and whenever I found myself
			indecisive about what to order, particularly at 
			dubious-looking places, I always defaulted to that
			tasty comfort dish.
			Easy to make and convenient to eat
			on-the-go, I decided to recreate it as my first <span
			       class="nm">Lila, Chop!</span>
		       savoury recipe.
		</p>
