		<h3>
			Recipe Tips 
		</h3>
		<p>
			To make this recipe vegan, simply skip the halloumi cheese. 	
		</p>
		<p>
			One of the photos shows this Mediterranean veggie wrap
			served with a Thai Omelette and broccoli.
			This was because a certain someone for whom I made this
			meal would hardly have found a veggie wrap enough for
			a post-workout dinner.
			So if you want to up the nutritional value and protein
			content of this dish, simply make a 3-egg omelette (2
			eggs + 1 egg-white) and serve with steamed broccoli on
			top. 
			The nutritional value will then be: 553cal, 28g
			protein, 23g carbs &amp; 40g fat.  
			(Don't let the amount of fat scare you; it's all
			healthy fats!)
		</p>
